# HTTP Credential Theft Analysis (Wireshark)

## Objective

Detect and extract credentials transmitted over unencrypted HTTP traffic.

## Lab Setup

* Kali Linux (Wireshark)
* Windows 10 (client)
* Metasploitable3 (web server)

## Steps

1. Start Wireshark capture on Kali
2. Generate HTTP traffic:
   curl http://10.10.10.40
   Login using web browser in Windows and trying to log in
3. Apply filter:
   http
4. Follow HTTP stream

## Findings

* Credentials transmitted in clear text
* Example:
  username=admin&password=1234

## Conclusion

Unencrypted protocols expose sensitive data and should be avoided in production.
